<p> [<a href="#identifier_35_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_36_80959" class="footnote">Very absolutely true -- there's a maximal resolution to be had from optical microscope before the noise overwhelms the image ; and there's a maximal closeness to truth each mind can get. But most importantly, the mind is not immune to noise. If it were than any man could reach the truth after a number of steps -- and you'd count the steps to sort the minds, there'd be no difference in end result but merely a difference in time taken. Indeed a faster weaker mind (that did then more steps per unit time) could overcome in the field a stronger slower mind (that needed say half the steps, but they each took trice the time). This isn't how it goes, but rather, that optimal distance is achieved after a certain number of steps, past which there's madness. </p>
<p>Some people put out their best results after the first pass -- we call these idiots and morons, but Lewis called him dad. Fewer people put out their best results on the second pass, and it'd be this contingent we <a href=http://trilema.com/forum-logs-for-04-sep-2018#2471654>were recently discussing</a>. Third passes or more can be had, but this generally requires <a href=http://btcbase.org/log/2018-09-04#1847558>complicated machinery</a> (the deep reason the Republic's unavoidable) else <a href=http://btcbase.org/log/2016-05-14#1466554>dangers</a>.  [<a href="#identifier_36_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_37_80959" class="footnote">And utterly not for the better, as contemporary hyper-information duly attests -- idle old women today are so well informed as to "what goes on" in school that there's absolutely no school left whatsoever. Is it perhaps the case that Dad didn't know "what went on" because Dad understood it's none of his damn business, nor something he may have an opinion on ? [<a href="#identifier_37_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_38_80959" class="footnote">Hole in the ground for reeducating slaves in ye olde latifundia. [<a href="#identifier_38_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_39_80959" class="footnote">It is funny to alien eye, this pitiful state of confusion where the representative of a universally hated opressor perceives itself nevertheless somehow cute and puppy-ish when confronting the necessary eventual gallows. Somehow Hitler pointing out the war was made both necessary and entirely unavoidable by the continued existence of the british empire was never heard over there. "Somehow". [<a href="#identifier_39_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_40_80959" class="footnote">For "making money" aka "influencing people" in a certain sense of the term. It's a p