<p>Lewis not being worth the time, in the strict sense that Fribble had the choice of re-reading for the third time his sixth least favourite funny paper or else "coming forward" at Sir Nobody-on-a-stick's "execution" and chose the ever-so-slightly preferable alternative simply does not enter the specifically narrow field of vision, does it ? How could somebody not cared enough to piss on him if he was on fire!!! [<a href="#identifier_90_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_91_80959" class="footnote">Well then, I guess he's even now! Teaches Fribble right for not giving a shit, tee-hee! [<a href="#identifier_91_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_92_80959" class="footnote">All this faggotry is starting to get annoying. [<a href="#identifier_92_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_93_80959" class="footnote">Perhaps nobody gets laid enough in perfidious Albion. [<a href="#identifier_93_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_94_80959" class="footnote">It's nice to have the original author back, because I must confess the channeling of oxfordian priggishness was so accurate it was starting to turn me off the whole adventure. [<a href="#identifier_94_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_95_80959" class="footnote">This lossage need not last. [<a href="#identifier_95_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_96_80959" class="footnote">It absolutely is. Dulling the spear of spite is the coward's way out, exact equivalent of literary suicide. No, philistines must be despised, that being the engine whereby the loss of goodness wrong upon good taste by its own awakening is at some length remedied. By similarity -- the goodness of a boy who is also a march lord is somewhat degraded by that boy's discovery that he can s