<p>There is ordinarily a world past the shackles, there is unsurprisingly a world outside the cave. Glorious gifts my eye. [<a href="#identifier_137_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_138_80959" class="footnote">This is a newfound, but just as intolerable, manner to prig out! Holy hell really, homely-cabbages-what-could-be-better ? Proceed without me, ye sailors of the Affectation sea, gloriously gifted of distances and (the more I read, the more it seems) one long carrot shared by two butts. [<a href="#identifier_138_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_139_80959" class="footnote">You may think "oh, no, it was well skilled -- such canisters of chlorine gas and wonders chemical!" but he is right in the sense he means it -- unskilled for the skill of the combatants mattered little, all men reduced to emulating on their expensive, dear flesh something very like a chicken, or at least something about a chicken's worth. [<a href="#identifier_139_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_140_80959" class="footnote">I don't believe it does. [<a href="#identifier_140_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_141_80959" class="footnote">This stabbing talk is rousing to sound most Freudian. [<a href="#identifier_141_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_142_80959" class="footnote">The original author notes that<br />
<blockquote>i.e. not necessarily and by its own nature. God can cause it to be such a beginning.</p></blockquote>
<p> [<a href="#identifier_142_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_143_80959" class="footnote">Self-deprivation. [<a href="#identifier_143_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_144_80959" class="footnote">It is probably true to some degre ; but some respite from the current situation would hurt nothing at all -- which is why I believe a system whereby nine in ten boys die before their adolescence ends while the remainder pick a few mistresses for their own dungeon off the field would be rather a breath of fresh air compared to the pantsuited swamp of "security" and what-else-is-it. At least the ensuing poetry would be much more readable than <a href=http://trilema.com/2014/the-mobile-revolution-or-what-consumers-have-come-to-expect/>the current crop</a>. [<a href="#identifier_144_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_145_80959" class="footnote">I am willing to bet he did not get even remotely close to the end. The end's not Victorianly "civlised" accuplation in any sense. [<a href="#identifier_145_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_146_80959" class="footnote">Cute, huh. [<a href="#identifier_146_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_147_80959" class="footnote">How about not so to call it, seeing how "I had learned something from Kirk about the honour of the intellect and the shame of voluntary inconsistency". Aiite ? [<a href="#identifier_147_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_148_80959" class="footnote">That anyone could be bothered with "Romanticism" ("faith" being just a subspecies of that boyish preoccupation, much like "socialism" is just another name for neotenic myopia) and at the same time know and like experience for what it is, that one could have ever heard the true ring of the world's silver and yet dive, seek out deliberately and dive in large piles of diformous zamak remains to me a great, incomprehensible puzzle. It's not unlike someone capable at the same time to draw the succession of thermodynamic curves composing the Carnot cycle and also willing to swear it's little gnomes under the hood making the wheels go with complicated rubber band attachments. </p>
<p>Not that I begrudge anyone the entomological interest, "this is the idiocy of those people, this is the folly of these people, this is the..." It is forbidden to teach a course in nonsense! To actually believe oneself an Assyrian, centaur, christian, theosophist, magician, dervish, whatever ?! There's something missing here. [<a href="#identifier_148_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_149_80959" class="footnote">George MacDonald of all god forsaken things! George MacDonald, that tedious twaddletoad a consummate moron like Oswald Chambers would defend in the most offensive of terminology! "It is a striking indication of the trend and shallowness of the modern reading public", bubbles the sludge, "that George MacDonald's books have been so neglected". Mark the <del>man</del> spandrel in attempt of stealing his very theft along with the wares he stole, prancing about in words that may only ever be directed at him, never by him. It is a striking indication of the imbecile cluelessness of Oswald Chambers, that he imagines poisonous turdology of this ilk could ever pass muster!</p>
<p>Here, this is what was "neglected" :</p>
<blockquote><p>The king sat on his throne<br />
            Glowing in gold and red;<br />
         The crown in his right hand shone,<br />
             And the gray hairs crowned his head.</p></blockquote>
<p>Is this some kind of practical joke ?! [<a href="#identifier_149_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_150_80959" class="footnote">This, I have lived, and <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/the-perfect-day/>inexplicably survived</a> ; yet I do not for a second credit the Donegal worthy of mention in this line. None can stand and challenge before the mighty, the incredibly grandiose, perhaps the sole, solitary grandeur of its kind in the whole Universe. Think about it -- it is entirely possible, and as far as we know it is entirely certain, that no greater ocean than the Pacific exists in this world. Not "this world" of provincial british fops and moth-ridden armchairs. This world, <em>this</em> one, the world of 10<sup>23</sup> stars and 10<sup>80</sup> atoms. The world, the true, the vast. The fine-as-it-is, the keep-your-teacups-to-yourself world.</p>
<p>Speak not to me of Donegal. [<a href="#identifier_150_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_151_80959" class="footnote">Beatings, savage, merciless, obliterating beatings cure this ; so thoroughly in fact the beaten slave does not even recall, years later, she ever had the problem, or how it was cured. Not alone, of course, and not "by themselves", of course. [<a href="#identifier_151_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_152_80959" class="footnote">This is as splendid a description of a tour in the Great War as one could ever dream to have. I was beginning to fear he'll just skip it entirely, but no, one short paragraph. Three cheers. [<a href="#identifier_152_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_153_80959" class="footnote">Fake it till you make it, eh ? I was wondering when the consumerist horn of the narcissist's head will raise into the moonlight.</p>
<p>This, incidentally, might be why I don't like boys -- a cause altogether similar in substance to why I don't share Al. Schwartz' passion for stinkweeds : their biology has needs which, while perhaps perfectly legitimate, nevertheless offend my senses. [<a href="#identifier_153_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_154_80959" class="footnote">I thought "everyone agreed" war is unfair and "irrational" (if these cumrags were older they'd have called it "hypocritical", no doubt) and bla bla bla. That whole nonsense reminded me of a brief encounter in my own country, back when I was an immoderately powerful young swain. </p>
<p>This was before the draft had been abolished ; most of my friends, or at any rate most of the young men in comparable circumstances were very keen to go "to army", because in their case it meant specifically a regiment set aside where whores and bottles were ferried in on weekly truck beds, and (I suspect) nobody really had to wash, especially if they didn't feel like it. I did not want to go (and, I suspect, unlike the majority I didn't <em>have</em> to go, perfectly able as I was to summon said delights one or two or five better on my own and without pretext). There was no one alive who could have overuled my decision in the matter ; I carried it through, obtaining such piles of entirely fabricated paperwork as to discourage civil servants through the sheer excess of size -- the message very plainly carried in subtext being that if you fuck with a boy who can summon up this tsunami, you will perhaps in short order encounter also the man. And he might carry a flaming axe and crack open your skull to use the crevice for a urinal.</p>
<p>But nevertheless, before I didn't go I still went, to take some kind of personal cognizance or I don't remember what the hell it was. There I met a dozen or two boys, exactly my age, picked randomly in any sort of sense (alphabetically, what can be randomly-er ?). I had never before encountered the common man, not in this sort of sense, rurals, nobodies, working class boys, the scummy base of the country. Out of sheer cruelty, not even seeking to amuse myself but rather out of the same impulse that drives a boy to tear a spider's legs one by one, merely to see how many does it <em>really</em> need to still climb the wall, a dispassionate cruelty entirely like what built up modern medicine (as opposed to contemporary -- modern, the sort with dissection chambers and "we can't start listening to the patients now") I proceeded to sink their forming agreement that "this sucks" and "it's a waste of time" and "they'd have better things to do" and "irrational" and bla bla bla. I said the words, "so go learn to shoot a rifle, it won't kill you" and other such things which they couldn't possibly detach from the most plain (and to them self-evident) good sense. I drove their "obvious" nonsense to just as obvious contradictions. I...</p>
<p>It was as cold an exercise in domination as you could ever have -- emulating their childish, simple heads inside my own took scarcely any effort while they couldn't even understand what the fuck's happening, a thoroughly nightmarish state. They huffed and puffed and were overrun with hurt feeling. Inferiority, as a helplessness, surged from the very ground and swelled and choked them. Oh, they hated me so ; eventually, driven by sheer despair, one of them offered that "well, if you like it so much maybe they should draft you alone and let us be!" They all agreed, I smiled the thin smile of the man who owns the land upon which the cattle, clueless, walks and brays and fights and dies, and continued to think as little of these readily-forged agreements and worthless consensuses as before, and as hence.</p>
<p>Do you know who agrees war is "irrational" ? <a href=http://trilema.com/republican-thesaurus/#footnote_4_39332>Boys</a> ; and they only. [<a href="#identifier_154_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_155_80959" class="footnote">Ah, to think WW1 promised such a great success of "solidarity" through mutually-agreed-upon throwing the curve by the rank and file! What wonderful world of peace, progres, prosperity &#038; pizda ma-tii could've built upon its "lessons", the tiresome old bags left at home. Awgh, awgh! [<a href="#identifier_155_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_156_80959" class="footnote">I can see it. [<a href="#identifier_156_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_157_80959" class="footnote">Very drastically not what Homer wrote about. That was the war of heroes, with men following in their train ; this was the war of bureaucrats, the Latin war, the war won by spades not by spears. [<a href="#identifier_157_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_158_80959" class="footnote">The original author notes that<br />
<blockquote>The iron in Malory, the tragedy of contrition, I did not yet at all perceive.</p></blockquote>
<p> [<a href="#identifier_158_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_159_80959" class="footnote">He fucked some older woman for a while, the wife of some companion killed. Big whoop. [<a href="#identifier_159_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_160_80959" class="footnote">Perfection is irrespective of the subject, an altogether sound approach. I'd much rather dine with a competent thief and an accomplished leper than with a mediocre poet and a middling banker. [<a href="#identifier_160_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_161_80959" class="footnote">This is the strictly wrong relationship to have with women. [<a href="#identifier_161_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_162_80959" class="footnote">I have no idea why all these louts seem to have among themselves decided poverty somehow at some point became socially acceptable, and the poor man may go as far as to profer opinions and discuss things as if he too, somehow, were a person. A poor man is a person in the exact sense a mouse is a bat : they both equally well feed a cat. [<a href="#identifier_162_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_163_80959" class="footnote">Approximately today's "treasuries", the "consols" ("Consolidated Stock", really inflationary fiat issuance through debt) and assorted other government paper constituded "the Funds", a source of income between three to five percent very highly regarded in the late 19th century for two reasons : one being that England suffered a long depression and the other being that they were slowly coming to overtake land as a source of income. There's little the runt dislikes more than <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/the-story-of-the-bitter-thorn-and-other-terrors/#selection-139.362-139.392>the indignity of existence</a>, and there's little more aptly symbolic thereof than productive use of land. In any case, they carried no principal guarantee, meaning in practice that almost no one involved ever extracted a genuine profit (except of course for the government, which thereby financed both its bureaucratic wastage and its martial adventures on the cheap). [<a href="#identifier_163_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_164_80959" class="footnote">I can't believe he's going to start quoting this crap now. And for the purpose of transvestitism, at that! [<a href="#identifier_164_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_165_80959" class="footnote">This strange notion that they'll figure out what "leads into" what, somehow. How ? How is this supposed to work ? [<a href="#identifier_165_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_166_80959" class="footnote">This is not altogether a bad theory, except for it being reversed. The <em>sort of mind</em> which <em>is already insane</em> will spend a time doing marginally insane things before dipping into the abyss. Not "because he faffed about he then went insane" but very much "because he was going to go insane, before actually doing it he first faffed about". Not "because he slipped her a mickey at the party he then raped her in the alley" but rather "because he was going to rape her in the alley therefore he slipped her a mickey at the party". Sadly this reordering also erases most of the perceived "corrective value" of "being careful", much in the same way slight familiarity with statistics removes the life extending benefits of getting married. What can you do ? [<a href="#identifier_166_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_167_80959" class="footnote">I'm shocked no "aurea mediocritas" etcetera shows up in here. No meden agan ?! How come no meden agan! [<a href="#identifier_167_80959" class="footnote-