<p>Learn math or die before puberty. I don't care how harsh it "sounds", it's not fucking harsh, it's a blessing when compared to the alternative. [<a href="#identifier_172_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_173_80959" class="footnote">Eventually made a modern version of Chaucer. [<a href="#identifier_173_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_174_80959" class="footnote">Actually, he was a closeted homosexual who raised a daughter, got a divorce, and spent the rest of his life in a college dorm. [<a href="#identifier_174_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_175_80959" class="footnote">Funny how the very finer metal of the ancients is called "religious" to salvage the idiotic infatuation. One could, by a stretch, call these religious, sure -- but at a cost : that nothing even remotely like xtianity could ever be religion in any possible sense. [<a href="#identifier_175_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_176_80959" class="footnote">This is so stupid as to breach past an excuse pious fraudulence may provide into outright ridicule. It's one thing to claim one's drunken father's vomitorium scent "endearing" ; it's quite another to pretend his drunken stagger "acrobatic". [<a href="#identifier_176_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_177_80959" class="footnote">Donne's <a href=http://trilema.com/2014/a-conceit-or-the-importance-of-blogging/#selection-101.61-101.73>about as "religious"</a> as Shakespeare. Which, incidentally, has been well avoided throughout, he only figures in a lateral mention as if to assure us that the omission's deliberate rather than illiterate. Check out the long line of Langland and Nobody-on-a-stick and a repurposed cvasi-Donne, how they overpower Shakespeare and Voltaire and I suppose Villon never existed nor... ah, what's the use. Two and three quarters can certainly exceed a million and a half, for "particularly low values of the million", why the hell not.</p>
<p>Such idiocy... And what the hell's a chesterton ?! Shakespeare is the only English writer posessed of sense I have ever read ; not in the sense that others aren't at all sensible, but in the sense that they can't possibly stand comparison, exactly like the IC fab clean room's the cleannest room I ever saw, not in the sense your bedroom's dirty but in the sense that give me a fucking break already. [<a href="#identifier_177_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_178_80959" class="footnote">Hai cu ma-ta... [<a href="#identifier_178_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_179_80959" class="footnote">This ennumeration's beyond idiotic. Yes, Dante is "religious", in a particular, deeply subversive sense. It could be said without much error Dante's religious like Machiavelli is curteous, in the manner a disinterested weaver may use rotten snails to tint his wares, or crushed up beetles, or whatever other thing. Whatever other <em>thing</em>. Meanwhile Plato's "religious" in a deeply different sense, and one that precludes altogether the peculiar theosophism the author's fixated on, and with it the dry and dryly mocked formalisms Dante <em>employs</em>. Now who the fuck is this other hooker and how did Pascal get mixed in... is this like one of those lowly porriges made of cheap oats boiled in cheaper blood that nevertheless get a slice of more expensive bacon spread atop to persuade the poor dockworker into purchase ? What, pray tell, is this supposed link uniting Plato, Dante and Pascal ? "I want to believe" ? [<a href="#identifier_179_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_180_80959" class="footnote">Patrocles almighty, he's found a new belly button and well supplied with plenty of lint!</p>
<p>It doesn't even fucking work, examining your interest in a hussy does not <em>by itself</em> reduce the interest. Only if practiced by certain people in certain ways, and those certains have little to do with the examination and lots to do with themselves, self-referentially.</p>
<p>Moreover, follow the "logical implication" -- no declared faithful is therefore ever in communion with his church. [<a href="#identifier_180_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_181_80959" class="footnote">Bullshit. What, these women love themselves ? [<a href="#identifier_181_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_182_80959" class="footnote">The whole thing is wank, no more ; the story of a brave little train which climbed a hill and then climbed another hill and then climbed a third hill and then ran out of steam and climbed no more. The final hill was not more remarkable, as far as hills go, nor steeper nor taller nor better nor gooder nor godlier nor anything-er than the previous three. Here it just happeend the little engine no longer could, and thus here it stopped, and that was <em>its</em> end of the line. Not "an" and not "the", but merely "its" -- if it had more steam it'd have found "the true hill" further down the rail ; and had it less it'd have found it further up. There is absolutely nothing clever, there's nothing even at all remarkable or worth the mention in this tediously complicated game of turning one's own tail into a turned tail turning, "joy this" and "joy the other", but whatever, the lengthy book's almost to an end, I'm not going to clip it. Let it flow, meaninglessly nonsensical as it does, and that'll be an end to it. [<a href="#identifier_182_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_183_80959" class="footnote">In that same way exactly <a href=http://btcbase.org/log/2014-03-05#548022>Harrison Bergeron</a> is "intellectually satisfactory" : to the morons. <A href=http://trilema.com/2016/a-complete-theory-of-politics/#selection-63.78-73.1>Beta boi</a> Lewis yearns to be dissolved in the primordial vat, the mute yearn for silence (not their own -- everyone else's) and the blind for darkness.</p>
<p>It's despicable. [<a href="#identifier_183_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_184_80959" class="footnote">Exactly the other way around. [<a href="#identifier_184_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_185_80959" class="footnote">The original author notes that<br />
<blockquote>Not, of course, that I thought it a tutor's business to make converts to his own philosophy. But I found I needed a position of my own as a basis from which to criticise my pupils' essays.</p></blockquote>
<p>This is idiotic. I don't need "a position of my own" from which to criticise pupils' essays because I simply use the weaknesses in their expression <em>of themselves</em>. Similarily I do not need "a position of my own" from which to write a novel -- I simply set some characters in a box and let them <em>act out their own life</em>. </p>
<p>So yes, according to both me and <a href=http://trilema.com/2013/a-very-unfair-perspective/#selection-31.0-31.374>J. H. Newman</a> (and very likely Old Knock, too -- consider that his old master's evaluation of his own capacities came as a surprise to him! where Kirkpatrick applying the proper method thought Lewis is useless, Lewis himself thought he is a goat just like all the other goats) -- according to everyone but empathically not Lewis' own, thorougly watered down sense of scholarly responsibility, Lewis taught extraordinarily badly. He's part of that other decay of Oxford <a href=http://btcbase.org/log/2018-08-21#1843465>I had mentioned</a>, and an eminent part of it at that. Because no, you don't end up with imbeciles quite as stolid as <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/wood-impregnated-in-oil-a-metaphor/>Timothy Williamson</a> in a day, or in a year. You have to really work at it, for decades upon decades upon decades. You must select the idiots and throw out the superior generation after generation after generation. Apparently, you did. [<a href="#identifier_185_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_186_80959" class="footnote">Oh fucking hell. Really, "did Hegel do more than add mystifications to the "<a href=http://trilema.com/2016/there-has-not-yet-been-seen-a-simple-thing-even-if-were-drowning-in-simple-people/>simple</a>" idiocy of Berkeley?" Is that the question I am asked ?</p>
<p><a href=http://trilema.com/2011/hai-sa-facem-un-exercitiu/>Fucktard</a>. How, just <em>how</em> was this <em>stirpitura</em> ever allowed to teach ? [<a href="#identifier_186_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_187_80959" class="footnote">It's not nonsense at all -- Christianity as a historical narrative is very sensible, precisely apart from its self-conscious xtianity. Consider the case where the soviet state nominally subsumed Russian science for a few decades. We can therefore say "soviet science is very sensible, apart from its soviet character" if we for some batshit reason decided to use the wrong terminology. The claim to history of the particular bit of nonsense he entertains is just as spurious as all the others', and if we call Oxfords' logic professor "Wykeham" we do not therefore imply that either Ralph Fiennes is a logician, or inherited a lawn at Oxford, or should, or that Oxford's somehow about The Lego Batman Movie. </p>
<p>To make it plain : just as there is no relation between Plato's "religiousness" and christianity, just so there is absolutely no relation between "christianity" in this historical sense and anything an English speaker could possibly know (and especially one so intellectually lazy as to tell himself Berkley's a fine transation to english of a Hegel too difficult to read in German -- see the sin of "translation" yet ?). The only christianity that's both meaningful to this historical view and accessible today is spoken in <a href=http://trilema.com/2017/dupa-dealuri/>Romanian</a>, and perhaps Greek (but one has to carefully select). The only christianity that's both meaningful to this historical view and accessible today is to you utterly and permanently inaccessible. Come to terms with that rather than attempting "just as good" substitutions and "passible" ersatzen -- they do not work for your intended purpose as they couldn't possibly ever work, but they do cover you in the unmistakable sparke of ridicule. [<a href="#identifier_187_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_188_80959" class="footnote">This is starting to veer into <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/yes-bitch-i-would-bring-it/>Gala Galaction</a> areas of fuckwardry. Really bitch, the "hardest boiled atheist you knew" ? Fucking <em>testimonials</em>, and about things that <em>don't even have any bearing</em> !? That a muse's what spoke to Moses was never in dispute ; yes people of all ages held exceptional writing talent for their period, and some of them actually put recording instrument to recording medium. [<a href="#identifier_188_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_189_80959" class="footnote">This is perfectly true ; a way which the barbarians readily lose. [<a href="#identifier_189_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_190_80959" class="footnote">Such as... <a href=http://trilema.com/2018/double-indemnity-but-proper-like/#selection-3243.1-3243.19>Peru</a> ? It is not an idle question. Answer it. [<a href="#identifier_190_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_191_80959" class="footnote">And stupid ; I do not want or expect my characters to "act and think as I would have". It's funny that the inept philosopher reproduces in his "system" the avatars of the bad novelist. What is this idiotic reverse-MarySue ?! The child who had no idea of the shape of the leaves in the garden where he played daily strikes again ; and I hope you see what I mean when I say it's a congenital defect. [<a href="#identifier_191_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_192_80959" class="footnote">It is the sure sign of the culling candidate, that "what he finds inside" "appals him". Impalement should swiftly follow this "appalment". [<a href="#identifier_192_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_193_80959" class="footnote">Except by the broken. The broken manage to live "idealism" just fine ; and the blind manage living in darkness also. [<a href="#identifier_193_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_194_80959" class="footnote">The original author notes that<br />
<blockquote>i.e. Shakespeare could, in principle, make himself appear as Author within the play, and write a dialogue between Hamlet and himself. The "Shakespeare" within the play would of course be at once Shakespeare and one of Shakespeare's creatures. It would bear some analogy to Incarnation.
</p></blockquote>
<p>All this is shockingly pedestrian. [<a href="#identifier_194_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_195_80959" class="footnote">The <a href=http://trilema.com/2017/love-in-an-elevator/>erstwhile virgin</a>, <a href=http://trilema.com/2017/mom/>recently impregnated</a>, may assure her parents all she will that she "never went looking for the cocks". Those parents'd have to be rather simple fellows to "believe" such nonsense. There's nothing there to believe : of course the fenotypical gash in her side, redolent of implicit genomic meaning, went looking for the cocks. Whether "she", as a figment of their imaginations, as a shared political construct, as a nothing of any consequence in any case "knew" or "didn't know" what's going on... The maiden goes looking for a dong as part and parcel of what she is, and just so the idiot goes looking for his plug, that he calls it "god" or "socialism" or whatever the fuck else notwithstanding, the plug, the plug to take him out of the world, to deliver him from the overbearing burden of existence. There's a call of his kind towards the natural flowering of his kind and that's all there is to it ; else we might as well entertain flies' protests they didn't go looking for the fresly laid turd. [<a href="#identifier_195_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_196_80959" class="footnote">I am not. [<a href="#identifier_196_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_197_80959" class="footnote">This is one of the dumbest things people drive into the skulls of helpless children, in a manner exactly like any other pedophile's grooming. There's no relationship between goodness and interest. [<a href="#identifier_197_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_198_80959" class="footnote">The sticky sadness of the misfortunate proto-republicans...  [<a href="#identifier_198_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_199_80959" class="footnote">Quite very much so indeed. Besides, all this "I r has opinion" wank <a href=http://trilema.com/2017/the-practical-costs-of-hallucinated-freedom/>comes at significant cost</a> on top of the sheer tedium of its expression. [<a href="#identifier_199_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_200_80959" class="footnote">This is idiotic nonsense ; a diary must be kept. [<a href="#identifier_200_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_201_80959" class="footnote">The original author notes that<br />
<blockquote>The only real good I got from keeping a diary was that it taught me a just appreciation of Boswell's amazing genius. I tried very hard to reproduce conversations, in some of which very amusing and striking people had taken part. But none of these people came to life in the diary at all. Obviously something quite different from mere accurate reporting went to the presentation of Boswell's Langton, Beauclerk, Wilkes, and the rest.</p></blockquote>
<p>This happens to be exactly the point. "It's a good idea to keep a blog precisely because it's a good idea to confront, honestly, flatly, your own intellectual platitude, your own lack of flair and intuition, your own fundamental inability of producing text worth reading."  [<a href="#identifier_201_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_202_80959" class="footnote">There was a time when no one perceived he had the authority to lock the house of god ; consequently it was patrolled by these fellows with famously long pipes (so they could watch uninterrupted while smoking). Think of this for a second : how can there be such a thing as a church <em>someone locks</em> ? Why are you calling your mom's garage "a castle" ? There haven't been any churches in the ourdemocracy for many many years now. [<a href="#identifier_202_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_203_80959" class="footnote">Lay off, the church survives out of getting women, common women, the paste indistinct of humanity, interested. When it doesn't serve as the place for them to expose their daughters for mating (and also at the same time carefully measure how widely open each pair of adolescent knees exposing musk to the breeze) there's not going to be any religion at all, "organised" or otherwise. [<a href="#identifier_203_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_204_80959" class="footnote">This is a false dychotomy, I have no problem fucking women I've not married and I similarily have no problem dancing, singing, sacrificing, trembling, adoring... I go to church, just I sometimes go to gaze at the paintings, some other times to have my cock sucked, or to drip wax on topless slavegirls, or whatever the fuck else. Whatever the fuck else <em>occurs to <b>me</b></em>. It's not a matter of "pantsuit, with their pantsuits, the rest, with the rest". The pantsuit <b><a href=http://trilema.com/2018/discordatum-wormatiense/>get nothing</a></b>. Nothing <b>at all</b> whatsoever. [<a href="#identifier_204_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_205_80959" class="footnote">Had "the empire" happened to conquer Islam rather than India, he'd have said about the same thing he's saying now. Except, of course, slightly different. And had Palestine been immensely wealthy instead, similarly...</p>
<p>Christianity is a joke, lay off already. [<a href="#identifier_205_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_206_80959" class="footnote">Holy shit this man can't read yet does not feel disqualified from opineating. What the fuck "Hindusism" is he even talking about, does he have a bunch of tea tins in his economic modern kitchen, one painted "Hegel" and the other "Hindusism" ? Are they both done by the illustrator of Punch magazine ?! [<a href="#identifier_206_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_207_80959" class="footnote">I'll pass. [<a href="#identifier_207_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_208_80959" class="footnote">Read the fucking log. Unlike "the gospel", <em>that</em> is exactly like this, myth after myth become fact after fact. What now ? [<a href="#identifier_208_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_209_80959" class="footnote">It is a miserable lout with fused thumbs pretending "<a href=http://trilema.com/2016/%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%88%D0%BD%D0%BE/#selection-1031.0-1033.110>this is everywhere</a>" ; naught more, and a sickening display at that. [<a href="#identifier_209_80959" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li></ol>
              <div>
                <div class="alignleft">&laquo; <a href="http://trilema.com/2018/minigame-smg-august-2018-statement/">MiniGame (S.MG), August 2018 Statement</a></div>
